div.p: I'm a software developer with a passion for producing high quality solutions to real-world problems. I pick up new languages and ecosystems quickly and I am always learning!

ul.li: Weird: Weird is a distributed (meaning optionally peer-to-peer and federated) Content Management System (CMS), built to increase the agency of internet users.
Leaf Protocol: A work-in-progress, peer-to-peer data protocol built on the awesome Willow Protocol.
Fish Folk: Jumpy tactical 2D shooter: Technical director and primary developer.
Bones Framework: An easy-to-use game engine for making real games.
WGPU: Helped implement WebGL2 support, which was used in the Bevy game engine.
egui: Added the option to specify texture filters so you can display pixel art, and implemented custom paint-callbacks for WGPU.
